Requests for a license shall be made to the department and shall be accompanied by a United States postal money order or cashier's check drawn in favor of the State Treasurer in an amount established by administrative regulations of a minimum of one hundred dollars ($100) and a maximum of fifteen hundred dollars ($1,500). The license shall be issued when the following are properly submitted to the commissioner:
The annual report of the licensee and the annual mine map required in KRS 351.170 and 352.450;
A certification from the commissioner of the Department of Workers' Claims that the licensee has provided positive proof of compliance with the provisions of KRS Chapter 342;
A certification from the commissioner of the Department of Revenue that the licensee is not a "delinquent taxpayer" as defined in KRS Chapter 131;
Mine seal construction plan filed with the state and approved by MSHA;
Roof control plan filed with the state and approved by MSHA;
The ventilation plan required in KRS 352.020; and
An approved emergency action plan required by KRS 352.640.
